Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Slice @jalapeño{1} into thin rounds, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine shallot, as much jalapeño as you like, juice from 2 lime wedges (4 wedges for 4 servings), @sugar{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp}, @chili powder{1/4%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), a pinch of lime zest to taste, a squeeze of lime juice, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Drain @corn{13.4%oz can}, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Heat a large, dry pan (preferably nonstick; if not, add a drizzle of oil) over medium-high heat. Add corn and cook, without stirring, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Continue to cook, stirring, until charred, ~{3-4%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

> The drier your corn, the less likely it is to pop in the pan. If corn begins to pop, cover pan.

Heat @butter{1%tbsp} and a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%oz} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in @Enchilada Spice Blend{1%tbsp} and @chil powder{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings). Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook until liquid has mostly absorbed and pork is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reserving veggies, pour pickling liquid to taste into bowl with corn. Stir in a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, remaining chili powder, and a large pinch of salt and pepper. Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Fill tortillas with pork and corn. Top with crema and as many pickled veggies as you like. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.